The Senate Committee on Rules offered the following
substitute to SR 96:
A RESOLUTION
1 Commending the benefits and contributions of purebred dogs and recognizing May 1, 2025,
2 as Purebred Dog Day at the state capitol; and for other purposes.
3 WHEREAS, dedicated individuals in Georgia breed dogs to develop unique, predictable
4 characteristics that enable dogs to excel in a wide range of beneficial areas; and
5 WHEREAS, purebred dogs are living legacies of the cultures that created them, and
6 historically these dogs worked alongside their people and provided them companionship; and
7 WHEREAS, the service of these breeds continues today as they work alongside humans and
8 provide inestimable companionship as guide dogs, service dogs, conservation dogs, livestock
9 guardians, search and rescue dogs, earth dogs, police dogs, canine soldiers serving by the
10 sides of our military men and women, and guardians of family, home, and hearth; and
11 WHEREAS, purebred dogs have been of enormous help to medical science, serving as
12 models for many heritable human diseases, playing a role in humanity's understanding of the
13 human and canine genomes, and benefitting pharmaceutical research and development; and
- 1 -

